subSubSection.paragraph:
DIAGNOSIS. — Animal small, elongate. Valves very elevated, with rounded posterior region, convex lateral slopes, non-beaked. Tegmentum sculptured by grooves following outline of valve in lateral and postmucronal areas, with grooves continuing in longitudinal direction in central and antemucronal areas; colour pink with randomly-distributed white spots. Valve viii with sloped antemucronal area; mucro slightly pointed; postmucronal area straight with slightly convex distal margin (
Kaas & Van Belle 1990: 102
).

